<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <meta name="description" content="DNS Pilot privacy policy for the Store-safe Windows app.">
  <link rel="canonical" href="{{SITE_URL}}/privacy.html">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <title>DNS Pilot Windows Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <header><p class="eyebrow">DNS Pilot for Windows</p><h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p>Current Store-safe Windows build.</p></header>
    <section><h2>Data Collection And Tracking</h2><p>DNS Pilot does not collect personal data, track users, include analytics, use advertising identifiers, or include third-party tracking SDKs.</p></section>
    <section><h2>Local Data</h2><p>DNS Pilot stores custom DNS profiles, custom domain suites, benchmark history, language, and benchmark preferences locally on the Windows device.</p></section>
    <section><h2>Network Activity</h2><p>User-initiated benchmarks send DNS queries and optional TCP connection probes to selected resolvers and target domains.</p></section>
    <section><h2>System DNS Changes</h2><p>The Store-safe build does not silently change Windows DNS. Guided Apply copies DNS values and opens Windows Settings for the user to make the OS-level change.</p></section>
    <section><h2>Contact</h2><p><a href="mailto:{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}">{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}</a></p></section>
  </main>
  <footer><a href="index.html">Support</a></footer>
</body>
</html>
